/*
For loop :- The for loop in Java is used when we know the total number of iterations in advance .

Syntax :-
for (initialization ; condition ; increment/decrement) {
    // Code to be executed
}

Flowchart :-
1) Initialize loop variable
2) Check condition
3) If true → execute code → increment/decrement → check condition again
4) If false → exit loop
 */


// The program to print numbers from 1 to 5 is


public class For_Loop {
    public static void main (String[] args) {
        for (int i = 1 ; i<=5 ; i++ ) {
            System.out.println(i);
        }
    }
}


/*
// The program to print even numbers from 1 to 10 is

public class While_Loop {
    public static void main (String[] args) {
        for (int i = 2 ; i<=10 ; i+=2 ) {
            System.out.println(i);
        }
    }
}
 */
